Package io.loader.load3D Description

Contains all classes needed to load a 3D-skeleton.

To load one 3D skeleton, 4 input files are needed:

  • The raw binary data containing the shape's volume, where the shape is marked by a value bigger than 0, the background is labeled with 0.
  • An info file for the raw data, containing meta information about the shape's volume, for example: 
                            
                        Width 123
                        Height 95
                        Depth 379
                        WidthDim 1.46875
                        HeightDim 1.46875
                        DepthDim 1.00134
                        MinVal ^@
                        MaxVal ^@
                        BitsUsed 16
  • The raw data containing the shape's skeleton, where the skeleton is marked by a value bigger than 0, the background is labeled with 0.
  • An info file for the skeleton raw data, containing meta information about the shape's skeleton, as shown above.
